{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"pack":1},{"id":2,"title":3,"category":4,"description":5,"questions":6},"nyt-easy","Easy Mini-Style Trivia","Word play","Short, breezy questions in the spirit of a daily mini puzzle. Built for warming up.",[7,17,27,37,46,55,64,73,82,91],{"id":8,"prompt":9,"choices":10,"correctIndex":15,"difficulty":15,"explanation":16},"ne-1","Tropical orange-fleshed stone fruit, five letters:",[11,12,13,14],"Peach","Mango","Guava","Melon",1,"Mango — five letters, fits the clue.",{"id":18,"prompt":19,"choices":20,"correctIndex":25,"difficulty":15,"explanation":26},"ne-2","Largest planet in our solar system:",[21,22,23,24],"Saturn","Neptune","Earth","Jupiter",3,"Jupiter is the largest, with a mass greater than all other planets combined.",{"id":28,"prompt":29,"choices":30,"correctIndex":35,"difficulty":15,"explanation":36},"ne-3","Capital of France:",[31,32,33,34],"Lyon","Marseille","Paris","Nice",2,"Paris.",{"id":38,"prompt":39,"choices":40,"correctIndex":15,"difficulty":15,"explanation":45},"ne-4","Number of sides on a hexagon:",[41,42,43,44],"Five","Six","Seven","Eight","Hex- = six. Octagon has eight, pentagon has five.",{"id":47,"prompt":48,"choices":49,"correctIndex":35,"difficulty":15,"explanation":54},"ne-5","Which of these is a primary color?",[50,51,52,53],"Green","Orange","Yellow","Purple","The three primary colors of light are red, green, and blue; in paint they are red, yellow, and blue. Yellow is the only primary in this list.",{"id":56,"prompt":57,"choices":58,"correctIndex":25,"difficulty":15,"explanation":63},"ne-6","Author of 'Romeo and Juliet':",[59,60,61,62],"Charles Dickens","Jane Austen","Mark Twain","William Shakespeare","Shakespeare wrote it around 1595.",{"id":65,"prompt":66,"choices":67,"correctIndex":35,"difficulty":35,"explanation":72},"ne-7","Smallest U.S. state by area:",[68,69,70,71],"Delaware","Connecticut","Rhode Island","Hawaii","Rhode Island is about 1,545 square miles.",{"id":74,"prompt":75,"choices":76,"correctIndex":35,"difficulty":15,"explanation":81},"ne-8","Currency used in Japan:",[77,78,79,80],"Won","Yuan","Yen","Ringgit","The yen has been Japan's currency since 1871.",{"id":83,"prompt":84,"choices":85,"correctIndex":15,"difficulty":15,"explanation":90},"ne-9","Tallest mountain on Earth, measured from sea level:",[86,87,88,89],"K2","Mount Everest","Kangchenjunga","Denali","Everest stands at 8,849 metres.",{"id":92,"prompt":93,"choices":94,"correctIndex":35,"difficulty":15,"explanation":95},"ne-10","How many continents are there?",[41,42,43,44],"Africa, Antarctica, Asia, Australia, Europe, North America, and South America."],"uses":{"params":["pack"]}}]}
